******
[4] Tunisia, El Kef governorate, livestock
Date: Wed 13 Oct 2021
Source: Shemsfm [in Arabic, trans. Mod.SF, edited]
https://cutt.ly/gReJT6S


The head of the regional veterinary services of El Kef governorate, Hussein Al Razayqi, announced today [13 Oct 2021], in a statement to [Tunis Afrique Presse] that cases of bluetongue disease have been recorded among herds of livestock in the region.

Al Razayqi added that 5 foci of BT disease were discovered in the region, and he called on livestock breeders of cows and sheep to be vigilant and to adopt measures that prevent the breeding of insects, such as eliminating stagnant water and wet places that help the emergence of insects and their transmission to animals.

--
Communicated by:
