******
[5] Tunisia, Jendouba governorate, sheep, cattle
Date: Sat 9 Oct 2021
Source: Shemsfm [in Arabic, trans. Mod.SF, abridged, edited]
https://cutt.ly/UE8WX1D


The head of the regional veterinary services of Jendouba governorate, veterinarian Ridha Ben Omran, confirmed the registration of 10 outbreaks of bluetongue disease following the reception of laboratory tests of samples from cattle and sheep that proved the presence of serotype 4 of this disease within 3 communes: Oued Melliz, Ain Draham, and Balta Bou Aoune.

He added that the veterinary services had raised additional samples from 5 other suspected outbreaks and that this disease caused the death of only 6 sheep in the region.

--
